# audit-pii keepers — committed, public-safe.
#
# Lines matching any pattern in this file are filtered OUT of audit results
# (treated as false positives). These describe the SHAPE of safe contexts —
# generic substrings only, no real names or identifying strings.
#
# Format: one ERE regex per line. Blank lines and # comments ignored.

# Room name "family room" — a conventional room type label, not family-attributing
family room

# Entity ID naming convention for the family-room fixture (e.g. light.first_family_*)
first_family

# Generic "owner's bedroom" naming
first_owner_bedroom

# Date-range token that looks like an age range to the regex
Week 8-10

# New persona anchor slugs (post-scrub) — these are the *replacement* anchors
persona-household
persona-maintainer
persona-guests

# Files allowed to legitimately reference rejected patterns
antipatterns\.md
\.audit-pii-keepers
\.audit-pii-patterns\.example
